---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = 'Privacy Policy';
const description = 'Privacy policy for Color Helper — learn how your data is handled when using our free browser-based color tools. No accounts, no tracking, no uploads.';
const canonical = 'https://color-helper.com/privacy/';
---
<BaseLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  canonical={canonical}
>
  <div class="content-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-wrapper">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: <time datetime="2026-06-19">June 19, 2026</time></p>

        <h2>Our Privacy Promise</h2>
        <p>
          Color Helper is built around a simple principle: <strong>your data stays on your device</strong>.
          Every color tool on this website runs entirely as client-side JavaScript in your browser.
          No account creation is required, no session data is tracked, and no personal information is
          collected, stored, or transmitted.
        </p>

        <h2>What We Collect</h2>
        <p>
          Color Helper does <strong>not</strong> collect:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Personal information (name, email address, phone number)</li>
          <li>Account credentials (we don't have accounts)</li>
          <li>Browser fingerprints or device identifiers</li>
          <li>Session data or behavioral analytics</li>
          <li>Your color palettes, images, or design data</li>
          <li>IP addresses (beyond what Cloudflare's edge network requires to serve requests)</li>
          <li>Cookies for tracking or advertising personalization</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Image Processing</h2>
        <p>
          When you use the Image Color Picker tool, your images are processed entirely within your browser
          using the HTML5 Canvas API. Images are read from your local file system, processed pixel by pixel
          in client-side JavaScript, and never uploaded to any server. The image data stays on your device
          and is discarded when you close or reload the page.
        </p>

        <h2>Local Storage</h2>
        <p>
          The Palette Library ("My Palettes") tool uses the browser's localStorage API to persist saved
          color palettes across sessions. This data is stored exclusively on your device, never sent to
          any server, and can be cleared at any time through your browser settings (typically under
          "Clear site data" or "Clear local storage"). We cannot access, view, or recover your saved
          palettes — they are yours alone.
        </p>

        <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>
          Color Helper uses the following third-party services, each with a specific, limited purpose:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Cloudflare Pages</strong> — Our hosting provider. Cloudflare handles CDN delivery,
            DDoS protection, and edge caching. Cloudflare's network logs may include IP addresses and
            request metadata for operational security. These logs are retained according to Cloudflare's
            privacy policy and are not accessible to us for analytics purposes.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Google AdSense</strong> — We display non-intrusive, contextual advertisements on
            tool pages to cover hosting costs. Google AdSense may use cookies and device identifiers
            to serve personalized ads based on your browsing history. You can opt out of personalized
            advertising at <a href="https://adssettings.google.com">adssettings.google.com</a>.
            AdSense is loaded only on tool pages (color picker, palette generator, converter, etc.)
            and not on guides, about, or privacy pages.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Google Fonts</strong> — We use Google Fonts for typography. When you load a page,
            your browser requests font files from Google's servers. Google may log your IP address
            for the purpose of serving these fonts. Refer to Google's privacy policy for details.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>IndexNow (Bing / Yandex)</strong> — When a new deployment is published, we
            optionally notify the IndexNow API to request re-indexing of our sitemap URLs. This
            submission includes only the list of public URLs to index — no personal data.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>GitHub</strong> — The source code for Color Helper is published on GitHub.
            If you submit a bug report or feature request via GitHub Issues, your GitHub username
            and the content of your submission will be publicly visible. This is optional and not
            required to use the tools.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Advertising &amp; Opt-Out</h2>
        <p>
          Google AdSense is our sole source of revenue. We deliberately chose a contextual,
          privacy-respecting ad model. You can:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Opt out of personalized ads at <a href="https://adssettings.google.com">adssettings.google.com</a></li>
          <li>Use an ad-blocker if you prefer an ad-free experience</li>
          <li>Use the tools without clicking any ads — there is no paywall, no premium tier, no usage limit</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Data Security</h2>
        <p>
          All connections to Color Helper are served over HTTPS via Cloudflare's edge network.
          We use HTTP Strict Transport Security (HSTS) with preload to ensure browsers always
          connect securely. Because we do not collect, store, or process personal data, there is
          nothing to lose in a data breach.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or
          applicable regulations (including the GDPR and ePrivacy Directive). Any changes will
          be posted on this page with an updated "Last updated" date. We encourage you to review
          this policy periodically. Material changes — such as the addition of analytics, tracking,
          or user accounts — will be communicated via a notice on the website.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about this privacy policy, data handling practices, or
          third-party services used on this site, please reach out:
        </p>
        <p>
          Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@color-helper.com">privacy@color-helper.com</a>
        </p>
        <p>
          We aim to respond within 5 business days.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .content-page {
    padding: 2rem 0;
  }
  .content-wrapper {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  h1 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }
  .last-updated {
    color: var(--color-text-tertiary);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  h2 {
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }
  p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }
  ul {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }
  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-size: 1rem;
  }
  a {
    color: var(--color-accent, #3b82f6);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
  strong {
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }
</style>
